author: SCOTT SUNDE
title: Bus burns on 405, jamming traffic
text:
A Sound Transit bus caught fire and burned Wednesday morning on northbound Interstate 405 near Interstate 90.
The Washington State Transportation Department said the fire was jamming traffic and making the Federal Way-to-Bellevue commute two hours.
Traffic cameras showed the bus engulfed in flames. The State Patrol says there were no injuries and that the fire may have started in a rear tire.
Fire crews managed to put the blaze out.
The bus was blocking the right lane and off-ramp. It was cleared before 10 a.m.
